<TITLE> Passengers stranded mid-river, cars pile up as fog halts ferries </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 4 (bdnews24.com)  Hundreds of vehicles were stuck on both banks of the Padma and around 1,000 passengers stranded mid-river amid dense fog as ferry services were disrupted between Mawa-Kawarakandi and Daulatdia-Paturia through Saturday night and Sunday morning. Sirajul Islam, manager of BITTC in Mawa told bdnews24.com: "Ferry service was totally disrupted for six hours between Mawa and Kawrakani from 3am to 9am." "Five ferries with around 1,000 passengers got stranded in the middle of the Padma," said Islam. "Over two hundred vehicles were stuck on two sides of the river." He said at least 165 river vessels including 12 launches were also stranded in the middle of Dhaleshwari, Meghna and Padma due to thick fog. "Passengers suffered amid the biting cold." Arpon Kumar, manager of BIWTC in Daulatdia, told bdnews24.com: "Ferry service was halted for five hours between Daulatdia and Paturia due to shortage of ferries and deep fog from 1am to 6am." Severe traffic congestion occurred on both sides of the route as over five hundred vehicles were backed up due to heavy fog and two ferries were out of order, said Kumar. Passengers were stuck in the bitter cold, he added, echoing Islam. bdnews24.co
